1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,500
Is a stranger looking at your
Facebook photos right now?

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,000
They might be. Here's how to
stop that in five minutes.

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,000
Open Facebook on your phone.
Tap your profile photo.

4
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:11,500
Tap Settings and Privacy,
then tap Settings.

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Scroll down and tap
Audience and Visibility.

6
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:18,500
Tap Posts. Change who can see
your posts to Friends only.

7
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Now tap Profile Information.
Find your friends list setting.

8
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,500
Set it to Only Me. This stops
scammers targeting your friends.

9
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,500
Go back. Find "How people
find and contact you."

10
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Set your email and phone number
lookup to Friends only.

11
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,000
That's your Facebook
locked down. Now Instagram.

12
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:39,500
Tap your profile photo.
Tap the three lines top right.

13
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Tap Settings and Privacy,
then Account Privacy.

14
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:46,500
Switch on Private Account.
Only approved followers see you.

15
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,500
One more thing — if you get
a request from a "friend" —

16
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
check your friends list first.
Scammers clone real profiles.

17
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:58,000
They use real photos to trick
the people who know you.

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:02,000
You've protected your privacy
on two platforms in five minutes.

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:05,500
For the full guide
with screenshots —

20
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:07,500
visit TekSure.com.
